SYSTEM FLOW DIAGRAM:
[Client Terminal] ----> (Network Connection) ----> [Server] 
[Server] ----> (Spawns a new Thread) ----> [Client Handler]
[Client Handler] ----> (Locks & Safely Updates) ----> [Shared Mailbox]
[Shared Mailbox] ----> (Triggers Save) ----> [Persistence Manager] ----> (Writes to Disk)


SERVER SETUP:
1. Start main program: [Server.java]
2. [Server] ----> Initializes central [Shared Mailbox]
3. [Server] ----> Tells [Persistence Manager] to load old messages from disk
4. Listen for incoming clients.
5. Loop: When a client connects...
    a. [Server] ----> Creates a dedicated [Client Handler Thread]


CLIENT HANDLER (One Thread runs for each connected user):
1. Loop: Wait for command from [Client Terminal]
2. If command is SEND:
    a. [Client Handler] ----> Locks the [Shared Mailbox]
    b. [Client Handler] ----> Writes message to the specified users' inboxes inside [Shared Mailbox]
    c. [Client Handler] ----> Unlocks the [Shared Mailbox]
    d. [Client Handler] ----> Sends "Message Sent!" back to [Client Terminal]
3. If command is READ:
    a. [Client Handler] ----> Locks the [Shared Mailbox]
    b. [Client Handler] ----> Copies messages from [Shared Mailbox]
    c. [Client Handler] ----> Unlocks the [Shared Mailbox]
    d. [Client Handler] ----> Sends formatted messages back to [Client Terminal]
4. If command is DELETE:
    a. [Client Handler] ----> Locks the [Shared Mailbox]
    b. [Client Handler] ----> Removes a message from [Shared Mailbox]
    c. [Client Handler] ----> Unlocks the [Shared Mailbox]
    d. [Client Handler] ----> Sends "Message Deleted" back to [Client Terminal]


CLIENT TERMINAL (What the user sees):
1. Start program: [Client.java]
2. [Client Terminal] ----> Connects to [Server] over the network
3. Display Menu and Loop:
    a. User types a command (like SEND or READ)
    b. [Client Terminal] ----> Sends command string over network to [Client Handler]
    c. [Client Terminal] <---- Receives the printed response from [Client Handler]
    d. Show response on screen.
